##########################################
### Instructions to run the simulation ###
##########################################

1) Load SmartBuilding.prj within MATLAB Environment. This will add the project folders to the MATLAB Path.

2) Run smartBuildingGUI.m script.

3) Set "Number of the rooms" to 3 and "Configuration" to 3000 for perfect sensor conditions, then click "Run".

4) Click help button for other configurations and their definition.

5) You can change physical system properties as you wish.

6) Results will be located in /Data/results

7) You can use plotTool for plotting the results. Within the plotTool, double-click "SimOut.mat" file. This will allow the simulation variables to be loaded into base workspace.
Then while you are pressing "Ctrl" button, select axisX and variable that you wish to plot.